HOW TO EXTRACT:
===============
Right click part01 and click Extract Here. DO NOT TOUCH THE OTHER PARTS. They will automatically extract all files.
Use 7-zip to extract(free) or
Winrar(you know where to get it)

Install:
=========
Extract the folder &quot;Counter-Strike Source&quot; to anywhere you want. 
Create a shortcut to HL2.exe with the following parameters:
(change resolution to your liking)
-game cstrike -dxlevel 90 -width 1920 -height 1080 -autoconfig

This should be in the target box, so it would look like:
&quot;C:Counter-Strike Sourcehl2.exe&quot; -game cstrike -dxlevel 90 -width 1920 -height 1080 -autoconfig

So it should look like this: &lt;a href=&quot;
http://i.cubeupload.com/0ljPmU.jpg&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://i.cubeupload.com/0ljPmU.jpg&lt;/a&gt;

Play!

NOTE!
=====
If you get runtime errors loading a map, then it is not compatible with the old engine. However, if you can play a custom map and get runtime errors, 
try to lower your resolution. Installing C++ Redist 2005 may help.
